###########################################################################
#  text_ligatures_kerned - exercises the interaction between AFM kerning   #
#  pairs (e.g. "AV", "Wa", "To") and OpenType ligature substitutions       #
#  (fi, fl, ffi, ffl) in a single Times-Roman paragraph.  Both back ends   #
#  read the same AFM kern table and the same ligature allowlist            #
#  (svg_font_has_ligatures), so the kerned-then-ligatured run should land  #
#  on identical pixel positions in PS and SVG.                             #
###########################################################################

@SysInclude { doc }
@Doc @Text @Begin
@PP
AVA WaVe ToTal -- kerning pairs followed by the four standard
fi fl ffi ffl ligatures in Times-Roman.  The sentence "AVAILABLE
final affinity" combines both: an "AV" kern pair, an "fi" ligature
in "final", and an "ffi" ligature in "affinity".
@End @Text
